data.chText: （某学科或专业的）报纸，刊物，杂志
data.enText: a newspaper or magazine that deals with a particular subject or profession
used in the title of some newspapers
a written record of the things you do, see, etc. every day

data.chText: 他把自己的亚洲之行记录下来了。
data.enText: He kept a journal of his travels across Asia.

simple_means.memory_skill: journ 日期 + al 表物 → 日报；杂志

ex.enText: I subscribed to a journal this year.

synonyms.bx: 指定期发行的周刊、月刊、季刊等，多指学术或专业团体出版的刊物或学报。

ex.chText: 这本杂志发行量很小/很大。
ex.enText: This magazine has a small/large circulation.

ex.chText: 她拿起一本杂志，看了起来。
ex.enText: She picked up a magazine and began to read.

synonyms.bx: 指登载各种文章、图片等的刊物，通常指周刊或月刊。

ex.chText: 她接受了《奥林匹克回顾》的采访。
ex.enText: She gave an interview to Olympic Review.

synonyms.bx: 指主要登载评论性、探讨性文章的刊物。

ex.chText: 他有每天写日记的好习惯。
ex.enText: He has the good habit of keeping a diary.

ex.chText: 船长把旅途中的事件记在日志中。
ex.enText: The ship captain kept a diary of the trip's events.

synonyms.bx: 指对每天所发生的事情或工作日程的记录。

ex.chText: 这是他在第二次世界大战期间的生活记事。
ex.enText: This is the chronicle of his life during World War II.

ex.chText: 这部编年史分为6个部分。
ex.enText: The chronicle breaks down into six parts.

synonyms.bx: 指对一系列事件按发生先后顺序所作的记录，尤指对历史事件的记录。

ex.enText: He began to keep a journal/diary when he was 10 years old.

ex.chText: 萨拉在日记中倾诉心事。

synonyms.bx: 指对每天所发生的事情的记录，可与 diary 换用。

ex.chText: 飞行员在其飞行日志中描述了这次引擎故障。
ex.enText: The pilot described the engine failure in his log.

synonyms.bx: 尤指航海日志、飞行日志或航行记录。

ex.chText: 把你已经买了的东西都记下来。
ex.enText: Keep a record of the things that you've bought.

ex.chText: 只有经理才能接触到销售记录。
ex.enText: Only the manager has access to sales records.

synonyms.bx: 指记录在纸张、胶片等上或存储在计算机中的与某事物相关的信息，以备将来查阅。

tr: the part of the axle contained by a bearing
a record book as a physical object
a daily written record of (usually personal) experiences and observations
a periodical dedicated to a particular subject
a ledger in which transactions have been recorded as they occurred

value.def: A journal is a magazine, especially one that deals with a specialized subject.

example.ex: All our results are published in scientific journals.
example.tran: 我们的研究结果全都发表在科学刊物上了。

value.tran: （尤指某专门学科的）杂志，刊物

value.def: A journal is a daily or weekly newspaper. The word journal is often used in the name of the paper.

example.ex: He was a newspaperman for The New York Times and some other journals.
example.tran: 他是个记者，为《纽约时报》和其他一些报刊撰稿。

value.tran: 日报，周报，…报（常用于报纸名称中）

value.def: A journal is an account which you write of your daily activities.

example.tran: 萨拉在日记中倾诉心事。

example.ex: On the plane he wrote in his journal.
